{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:job.17",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 17,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 17",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 17 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:job.17.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 17:1",
      "text": "“My spirit is consumed. My days are extinct and the grave is ready for me.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.17.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 17:2",
      "text": "Surely there are mockers with me. My eye dwells on their provocation.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.17.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 17:3",
      "text": "“Now give a pledge. Be collateral for me with yourself. Who is there who will strike hands with me?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.17.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 17:4",
      "text": "For you have hidden their heart from understanding, therefore you will not exalt them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.17.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 17:5",
      "text": "He who denounces his friends for plunder, even the eyes of his children will fail.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.17.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 17:6",
      "text": "“But he has made me a byword of the people. They spit in my face.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.17.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 17:7",
      "text": "My eye also is dim by reason of sorrow. All my members are as a shadow.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.17.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 17:8",
      "text": "Upright men will be astonished at this. The innocent will stir himself up against the godless.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.17.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 17:9",
      "text": "Yet the righteous will hold to his way. He who has clean hands will grow stronger and stronger.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.17.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 17:10",
      "text": "But as for you all, come back. I will not find a wise man among you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.17.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 17:11",
      "text": "My days are past. My plans are broken off, as are the thoughts of my heart.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.17.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 17:12",
      "text": "They change the night into day, saying ‘The light is near ’ in the presence of darkness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.17.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 17:13",
      "text": "If I look for Sheol as my house, if I have spread my couch in the darkness,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.17.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 17:14",
      "text": "if I have said to corruption, ‘You are my father,’ and to the worm, ‘My mother,’ and ‘My sister,’",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.17.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 17:15",
      "text": "where then is my hope? As for my hope, who will see it?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.17.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 17:16",
      "text": "Shall it go down with me to the gates of Sheol, or descend together into the dust?”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
